value: Breeds in Scandinavia north of the Arctic Circle, northern Russia south to Moscow, Kazan and Orenberg, and in northern Asia east to Kamchatka. Winters south to Africa, India, Burma, China, Japan and the Malay States.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Palearctic winter visitor, inland and coastal waters: all around Sahara south to Cameroon - C Tanzania.
Marshy sites in bushy tundra and edge of the taiga (breeding); marshes, ponds, wet meadows, and mudflats (nonbreeding).
